      <link>https://www.instagram.com/p/DVGVoeVjHi6/</link>
      <description><![CDATA[<p><img src="https://scontent-cph2-1.cdninstagram.com/v/t51.82787-15/642152129_18568874404027532_7808520636064176004_n.jpg?stp=dst-jpg_e35_tt6&amp;_nc_cat=106&amp;ig_cache_key=MzgzODg0OTcyNTg5NDQ5Njk3OQ%3D%3D.3-ccb7-5&amp;ccb=7-5&amp;_nc_sid=58cdad&amp;efg=eyJ2ZW5jb2RlX3RhZyI6InhwaWRzLjEwODB4MTM1MC5zZHIuQzMifQ%3D%3D&amp;_nc_ohc=gpoprlBE53sQ7kNvwGFkv7d&amp;_nc_oc=Adq_SfWESgtuKbxD8CyR03NJlnJFWFUO924zOdraBQEqZbf3HLQIEUF-KKC3F5FEZpk&amp;_nc_ad=z-m&amp;_nc_cid=0&amp;_nc_zt=23&amp;se=7&amp;_nc_ht=scontent-cph2-1.cdninstagram.com&amp;_nc_gid=c9DwnYTNdrgvjq7AxVjDtg&amp;_nc_ss=7a338&amp;oh=00_AfypclB_DcrM_PaGkMFxt9SNWBYT_KQJWS7JvcH_WS6kNg&amp;oe=69CA0264" alt="Slide 1 fra @annieatkins" style="max-width: 48%; margin: 0 1% 8px 0;" /><img src="https://scontent-cph2-1.cdninstagram.com/v/t51.82787-15/640916367_18568874413027532_2983734779848620589_n.jpg?stp=dst-jpg_e35_tt6&amp;_nc_cat=102&amp;ig_cache_key=MzgzODg0OTcyOTU4NTUyMzU3Mw%3D%3D.3-ccb7-5&amp;ccb=7-5&amp;_nc_sid=58cdad&amp;efg=eyJ2ZW5jb2RlX3RhZyI6InhwaWRzLjEwODB4MTM1MC5zZHIuQzMifQ%3D%3D&amp;_nc_ohc=tKwBs8wt9CYQ7kNvwFGE7z7&amp;_nc_oc=AdpCXic1ujgqN3DCS0FzZc0WFbfUooF7U_7pLldsdgGElhAaZ8OM9KUG-kk75IsHxlA&amp;_nc_ad=z-m&amp;_nc_cid=0&amp;_nc_zt=23&amp;se=7&amp;_nc_ht=scontent-cph2-1.cdninstagram.com&amp;_nc_gid=c9DwnYTNdrgvjq7AxVjDtg&amp;_nc_ss=7a338&amp;oh=00_AfzakX94L0M2kHyh8SQBoxgMaF1MCQMjJgRQ92p-AwLiPw&amp;oe=69CA11C9" alt="Slide 2 fra @annieatkins" style="max-width: 48%; margin: 0 1% 8px 0;" /></p><p><strong>🖼️ Slideshow (2 medier)</strong></p><p><strong>@annieatkins</strong></p><p>Making Belief<br/>
<br/>
A workshop in creating real objects for imaginary worlds<br/>
<br/>
I’ll be teaching on a ship in Norway this March, looking at how handmade artefacts—from film props to paper ephemera in children’s books—help fictional worlds feel lived-in. We’ll be aboard the MS Sandnes in Stavanger Harbour (docked, no sea legs required!).<br/>
<br/>
The Sandnes was never really a ghost ship... but never let the truth stand in the way of a good story. The trick to getting an audience on board any tall story is making each detail in the filmmaking process feel credible. Every designer on a film set does this: in costume it might mean giving actors the right shoes even when the camera never frames their feet; in graphics it’s putting the full stops in all the right places, even though nobody will consciously notice.<br/>
<br/>
If you’re in Norway and a member of Grafill, there’s a travel bursary you can apply for to get to Stavanger. If you’re travelling from outside Norway, you’d be very welcome to join us too.<br/>
<br/>
One-day workshops:<br/>
<br/>
6–7th March 2026<br/>
Stavanger, Norway<br/>
<br/>
Tickets are available only through @grafill_stavanger <br/>
<br/>
Boat drawing by @__clarabelle_</p><p><a href="https://www.instagram.com/p/DVGVoeVjHi6/">Se slideshow på Instagram</a></p>]]></description>
