      <description><![CDATA[<p><img src="https://scontent-cph2-1.cdninstagram.com/v/t51.82787-15/619614610_18088401173028905_6618293723700632026_n.jpg?stp=dst-jpg_e35_s1080x1080_sh2.08_tt6&amp;_nc_cat=105&amp;ig_cache_key=MjQ4NTA5NzA1MTMxNTMxMDM2Mg%3D%3D.3-ccb7-5&amp;ccb=7-5&amp;_nc_sid=58cdad&amp;efg=eyJ2ZW5jb2RlX3RhZyI6InhwaWRzLjExODB4MTE4MC5zZHIuQzMifQ%3D%3D&amp;_nc_ohc=8sznRx2-P9cQ7kNvwHWHaWg&amp;_nc_oc=AdoZtzBAs5PFGxJwEd_5hsXRrV3-NK0d3rlBsx7tW-y0KzGyF_VpRiR-m1Ifcnhsc8s&amp;_nc_ad=z-m&amp;_nc_cid=0&amp;_nc_zt=23&amp;_nc_ht=scontent-cph2-1.cdninstagram.com&amp;_nc_gid=c9DwnYTNdrgvjq7AxVjDtg&amp;_nc_ss=7a338&amp;oh=00_AfzGdEWpfksoQEdpm8x_ZulEF6p0LzUi2o4h6JHK7gmiPQ&amp;oe=69CA1AC7" alt="Instagram billede fra @annieatkins" /></p><p><strong>@annieatkins</strong></p><p>Carrying on from yesterday’s post, I feel I should point out that the real problem with tea-staining props is that the paper creases and the ink runs. There are ways around this (you can stain the paper first and then draw on top, or you could laser print) but nothing gets around the fact that ageing paper is, in fact, a massive pain in the arse. If I were ever to launch a product it would definitely be selling snake oil to film productions: with my special no-crease no-smudge formula! (The ointment pictured here is not real, I’m sorry. You can try neutral boot polish for a very similar effect though!).</p>]]></description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><img src="https://scontent-cph2-1.cdninstagram.com/v/t51.82787-15/619614610_18088401173028905_6618293723700632026_n.jpg?stp=dst-jpg_e35_s1080x1080_sh2.08_tt6&amp;_nc_cat=105&amp;ig_cache_key=MjQ4NTA5NzA1MTMxNTMxMDM2Mg%3D%3D.3-ccb7-5&amp;ccb=7-5&amp;_nc_sid=58cdad&amp;efg=eyJ2ZW5jb2RlX3RhZyI6InhwaWRzLjExODB4MTE4MC5zZHIuQzMifQ%3D%3D&amp;_nc_ohc=8sznRx2-P9cQ7kNvwHWHaWg&amp;_nc_oc=AdoZtzBAs5PFGxJwEd_5hsXRrV3-NK0d3rlBsx7tW-y0KzGyF_VpRiR-m1Ifcnhsc8s&amp;_nc_ad=z-m&amp;_nc_cid=0&amp;_nc_zt=23&amp;_nc_ht=scontent-cph2-1.cdninstagram.com&amp;_nc_gid=c9DwnYTNdrgvjq7AxVjDtg&amp;_nc_ss=7a338&amp;oh=00_AfzGdEWpfksoQEdpm8x_ZulEF6p0LzUi2o4h6JHK7gmiPQ&amp;oe=69CA1AC7" alt="Instagram billede fra @annieatkins" /></p><p><strong>@annieatkins</strong></p><p>Carrying on from yesterday’s post, I feel I should point out that the real problem with tea-staining props is that the paper creases and the ink runs. There are ways around this (you can stain the paper first and then draw on top, or you could laser print) but nothing gets around the fact that ageing paper is, in fact, a massive pain in the arse. If I were ever to launch a product it would definitely be selling snake oil to film productions: with my special no-crease no-smudge formula! (The ointment pictured here is not real, I’m sorry. You can try neutral boot polish for a very similar effect though!).</p>]]></content:encoded>
